{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/74178", "id": 446756281, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDQ2NzU2Mjgx", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74178", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74178.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/74178.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/74178", "number": 74178, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Add `std::io::input` simple input function.", "user": {"login": "sHaDoW-54", "id": 23418926, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjIzNDE4OTI2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23418926?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54", "html_url": "https://github.com/sHaDoW-54", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sHaDoW-54/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Condenses the normal input process into one function. This is good for new rust users who don't understand the normal process and for users who don't require special functionality.\r\n\r\nEspecially with new rust users looking to make small programs, input can be a tricky thing for them to grasp, especially when other languages do this much simpler.\r\n\r\nEX:\r\nPython : ```user_input = input(\"Enter: \")```\r\nRuby: ```user_input = gets```\r\nC#: ```user_input = Console.ReadLine();```\r\n\r\nSo this...\r\n\r\n```\r\nuse std::io::{stdin,stdout,Write};\r\nlet mut s=String::new();\r\nprint!(\"Please enter some text: \");\r\nlet _=stdout().flush();\r\nstdin().read_line(&mut s).expect(\"Did not enter a correct string\");\r\nif let Some('\\n')=s.chars().next_back() {\r\n    s.pop();\r\n}\r\nif let Some('\\r')=s.chars().next_back() {\r\n    s.pop();\r\n}\r\nprintln!(\"You typed: {}\",s);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWould turn into this...\r\n\r\n```\r\nuse std::io::input;\r\nlet user_input = input(\"Please enter some text: \");\r\nprintln!(\"You typed: {}\", user_input);\r\n```", "created_at": "2020-07-09T10:03:36Z", "updated_at": "2020-11-20T07:53:03Z", "closed_at": "2020-08-13T00:12:32Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "49d897cba4be2a7ef197c01b992bdf11f319994c", "assignee": {"login": "sfackler", "id": 1455697, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTU2OTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1455697?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler", "html_url": "https://github.com/sfackler", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "sfackler", "id": 1455697, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTU2OTc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1455697?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sfackler", "html_url": "https://github.com/sfackler", "followers_url": "https://api